    public class CompoundPredicate
extends AbstractPredicateImpl
implements java.io.Serializable
    A compound predicate is a grouping of other predicates in order to convert either a conjunction (logical AND) or a disjunction (logical OR).

      • render

        public java.lang.String render(boolean isNegated,
                               RenderingContext renderingContext)
        Description copied from interface: PredicateImplementor
        Form of Renderable.render(org.hibernate.query.criteria.internal.compile.RenderingContext) used when the predicate is wrapped in a negated wrapper. Allows passing down the negation flag.

        Note that this form is no-op in compound (junction) predicates. The reason being that compound predicates are more complex and the negation is applied during its creation.

        Specified by:
        render in interface PredicateImplementor
        Parameters:
        isNegated - Should the predicate be negated.
        renderingContext - The context for rendering
        Returns:
        The rendered predicate fragment.

      • not

        public javax.persistence.criteria.Predicate not()
        Create negation of compound predicate by using logic rules: 1. not (x || y) is (not x && not y) 2. not (x && y) is (not x || not y)
